(3, 'services.php', '<div class="page-title page-title-services bg-pattern" data-bgcolor="2791AA">\r\n		<div class="page-title-overlay">\r\n			<div class="container">\r\n				<div class="row">\r\n					<ol class="breadcrumb">\r\n						<li class="breadcrumb-home"><a href="index.php"><i class="fa fa-home"></i></a></li>\r\n						<li class="active">Services</li>\r\n					</ol>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<!--\r\n        ====================\r\n        START: MOBILE DESIGN\r\n        ====================\r\n    -->\r\n	<a href="tel:09 218 7777" class="fancybox-2 btn btn-default hidden-sm hidden-md hidden-lg hidden-xlg" id="header-call-button-spacing">\r\n            CALL US\r\n        </a>\r\n    <!--\r\n        ==================\r\n        END: MOBILE DESIGN\r\n        ==================\r\n    -->\r\n\r\n	<div class="services-1" id="services">\r\n		<div class="container">\r\n			<div class="row">\r\n				<h2 class="section-title text-center">\r\n					<span class="bold700">\r\n						We provide the full range of dental services\r\n					</span>\r\n				</h2>\r\n				<p>At The Dental Hub, we strive to make experience of our patient personalized and comfortable every time. Our clinic unites advanced dentistry technology with a preventative philosophy to accomplish not only healthy teeth and gums but confident, beautiful smiles. The Dental Hub work with a philosophy that “Best experience is the most valuable thing that we can offer to our patients” so Dentist and support staff of The Dental Hub try their level best to give best experience to each and every patient.</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<div class="serv">\r\n		<ul id="isotope-filter">\r\n			<li><a class="active" data-filter="*">All services</a></li>\r\n			<li><a data-filter=".general_dentistry">General Dentistry</a></li>\r\n			<li><a data-filter=".emergency_dental_treatment">Emergency Dental Treatment</a></li>\r\n			<li><a data-filter=".affordable_cosmetic_services">Affordable Cosmetic Services</a></li>\r\n			<li><a data-filter=".smile_makeovers">Smile Makeovers</a></li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		\r\n		<div class="container">\r\n			<div class="row">\r\n				<div class="serv-items" id="isotope-items">\r\n					<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n						<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n							<h3>Pain-free Treatment</h3>\r\n							<p>We understand that dental treatment is a painful experience but at The Dental Hub we always make sure that you our patients always get pain-free treatments after they get numb. They feel slight pinch of pain when we give an injection at the starting of treatment and assure you that the pinch also go within a minute.</p>\r\n							<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Routine Dental Exam</h3>\r\n								<p>The routine dental test about polishing and cleaning include x-rays test (taken once a year) is done just to make sure that there is no decays in between teeth. Scaling session make sure that your teeth are cleaned. All the deposits and debris are cleaned away from everywhere even in between your teeth and teeth are polished to give you a clean and even surface. It is recommended to get routine dental check up after every 6 months or a year for oral hygiene.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Scaling and Polishing</h3>\r\n								<p>Scaling is a process of getting your teeth cleaned using ultrasonic scalar which applies high vibrations and water to take out that unwanted deposits on your teeth. Polishing is done after scaling to make sure that no sharp points anywhere and your teeth is left behind.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Periodontal (Gum) Treatment</h3>\r\n								<p>Bleeding, sore gums, bad breath and loose teeth are something’s that you shouldn’t be living with and these are the few indications of periodontal sickness. After giving local anesthesia, proper cleaning is done at gum level at a time interval of 15 days. Patient has to keep up with the regular scale, check up, and polish and also maintain your oral hygiene routine at home.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Tooth Colour Fillings</h3>\r\n								<p>At times we often feel discomfort and pain when food stuck between our teeth due tooth decay or cavity. Situation like this can be easily fixed by filling and restoring the teeth. The basic idea behind a filling is to take out all the decayed part of your tooth and then fill it up. And now we have materials that are strong enough and can have the same shade as your natural teeth which will help you have that perfect smile as well as get rid of that decay. Patient can eat or drink immediately after the filling is done as the material will be set and shaped before you leave the clinic.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Root Canal Treatment</h3>\r\n								<p>Human teeth’s have canals in the center which act as connection for nerves and blood vessels. A deep decay, infection or any type of accident can cause harm to these blood vessels and cause you a lot of pain. A root canal treatment can help to treat this condition. In this scenario first we open up the canals, take out the septic blood vessels and nerves, clean up the root canal and at last fill it up with a filling material in-order to avoid any future infection. The whole treatment is done in span of 2 to 3 sittings.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Tooth Extraction</h3>\r\n								<p>If a tooth has been damaged by decay or broken by accident, at first instances we try to restore it with crown and filling. At times, damage is too much for the tooth to be repaired. In such a scenario, we try to make this ordeal as painless. We make sure that you are numb before starting any procedure and during the whole treatment time you are free to stop us at any time if you are having any pain or discomfort. We remove the teeth from its socket in the bone with precise and care. If you follow the pedagogies of The Dental Hub, you will not face any complications after tooth extraction in future.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Dentures</h3>\r\n								<p>Dentures are set of removable, substitute for missing teeth and surrounding tissues. They not only help you gain back your confidence but also enhance your ability to chew by replacing edentulous areas with denture teeth. As per your need, you can either have a partial denture to replace only the missing teeth or a full denture if you have lost all your teeth. Dentures are also available in various type of materials to help you get adjusted.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Veneers</h3>\r\n								<p>It is a layer of composite or dental porcelain material placed over a teeth, either to improve the esthetics of a teeth or to defend the tooth’s surface from impairment. They act as a shell that cover the external layer of your teeth and come in a variety of color shades which can be chosen to exactly match the color of your teeth.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Dental Crowns</h3>\r\n								<p>It is an artificial restitution that fits over the remaining part of prepared teeth, making it strong and giving it the shape of natural teeth. A crown is sometimes known as a ‘cap’. Unlike removable devices such as dentures, which are removable and clean daily, crowns are permanently fixed onto existing teeth or implants, and can only be removed by a dentist. Crown implantation requires two sitting with a gap of 15 days.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Dental Bridges</h3>\r\n								<p>IBridges are primarily used to replace one or more missing teeth. A bridge is made up of two or more than two crowns. Bridges are cemented to the natural teeth or implants surrounding the empty space. These teeth, known as abutments, act as anchors for the bridge. The procedure timing is similar to that for a dental crown.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Free WINZ Quotes</h3>\r\n								<p>The Dental Hub provide free consultation and treatment for Work and Income NZ quote so that you can get your teeth treated without worrying about how you are going to pay for your Emergency dental treatment.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Free treatment for under 18</h3>\r\n								<p>The Dental Hub provide free treatment for teenagers of the age group of 13 to 18. Children below 13 year of age either get a referral letter from their school dentist or they have to pay for the treatment.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Free ACC Treatment</h3>\r\n								<p>We are certified dentistry service provider of Accident Compensation Commission and we make sure that you get the care, you deserve after the terrible accident.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Teeth Whitening</h3>\r\n								<p>Teeth whitening process lighten up color of your teeth and help to get rid of discoloration and stains. This need to be repeated at regular interval to maintain the brighter color of your teeth. We also offer take home kits which can help you whiten your teeth at your comfort station.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Mouth Guards</h3>\r\n								<p>A mouth guard is a protective cushion that covers the gums and teeth to prevent and reduce the chances of injury to the gums, arches, teeth and lips. If you are a sports freak and you require a mouth guard to protect your teeth, we can make a customize mouth guard that fits you and let you concentrate on your game.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item general_dentistry">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Gold Teeth</h3>\r\n								<p>Do you want a golden smile on your face that can gain attention of everyone around you? We can help you achieve the same in just two sittings. We can put a gold crowns which will cover the whole of your teeth. This is a good option for those who have the habit of grinding teeth at night as this is one of the strongest crowns available in the market till date.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">General Dentistry</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Immediate Dentures</h3>\r\n								<p>An immediate denture is a partial or complete denture inserted on the very same day, immediately after the removal of natural teeth. The process involves taking your impressions and making the denture for you and then taking your teeth out. The denture can then be reset to conform to your recovered gums properly at a later stage. The Dental Hub provide immediate denture service on priority basis.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Broken/Chipped Tooth</h3>\r\n								<p>Minor chipped teeth can be treated with filling material same to the color of teeth in one sitting. If in case you have broken tooth we have the options like crowns and root canals etc which will help you get that lost tooth back.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Broken &amp; New Dentures</h3>\r\n								<p>We can add extra teeth to your existing dentures and fix your crack or broken denture in one single appointment. You just need to give your denture to us in the morning and you can pick it up by evening.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Dental Sport Injuries</h3>\r\n								<p>According to some report 13-39% of all dental injuries are sports-related due to blow by an object or hard fall on ground. Most common types of Injuries are</p>\r\n								<ul>\r\n									<li>Avulsed tooth</li><br>\r\n									<li>Luxated tooth</li><br>\r\n									<li>Fractured tooth</li>\r\n								</ul>\r\n								<p>We treat and take care of all kind of Dental Sport injuries</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Lost Dental Fillings &amp; Crowns</h3>\r\n								<p>We replace and fix old fillings and crowns that have come off or not fitting properly anymore.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Partial Tooth Dislodgement</h3>\r\n								<p>It is a condition when tooth is struck out of the mouth; it may be partially dislodged or fully disconnected from the socket. We can put back in place and treated with medicines for a few days which will help to re-establish the blood supply and to keep the tooth strong and stable.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Jaw Injuries</h3>\r\n								<p>This can happen due to Recreational or sports injury, attack, motor vehicle accident. Jaw injury is of two types</p>\r\n								<ul>\r\n									<li>A broken jaw is a break (fracture) in the jaw bone.</li><br>\r\n									<li>A dislocated jaw means the lower part of the jaw has moved out of its normal position at one or both joints.</li><br>\r\n								</ul>\r\n								<p>We treat and take care of all kind of Jaw injuries</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Toothache</h3>\r\n								<p>Toothache or tooth pain in or around a tooth that may be caused number of reason like :</p>\r\n								<ul>\r\n									<li>Tooth Decay</li><br>\r\n									<li>Infected Gums</li><br>\r\n									<li>Tooth Fracture</li><br>\r\n									<li>Poorly placed fillings or crowns</li><br>\r\n									<li>Abscessed tooth</li><br>\r\n									<li>Plaque</li><br>\r\n									<li>Repetitive motions, such as chewing gum or grinding teeth</li>\r\n								</ul>\r\n								<p>With regular dental checkups you can detect early infected gums and tooth decay and restore the teeth to avoid any pain in the future and also save a lot of money that will be required to treat a badly decayed tooth.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Dental Abscesses</h3>\r\n								<p>A tooth abscess or dental abscess, is an accumulation of excess pus that forms inside the gums. This is characterized by swelling on gums and severe pain. There are basically 3 types of dental abscess:</p>\r\n								<ul>\r\n								<li>Gingival abscess</li><br>\r\n								<li>Periodontal abscess</li><br>\r\n								<li>Periapical abscess</li><br>\r\n								</ul>\r\n								<p>This can be easily treated by a filling or root canal treatment depending on the findings on an x-ray report.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Infected Wisdom Teeth</h3>\r\n								<p>Most of times we fail to clean wisdom teeth as they are located in far end of mouth and it is difficult to take proper care of them. In such cases it is suggested to be filled or root canal treated in the other case it is advise to remove your wisdom teeth.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Impacted Wisdom Teeth</h3>\r\n								<p>A wisdom teeth that has not erupted into your oral cavity is called impacted. At times impacted wisdom teeth don’t show direct symptoms. However, when an impacted wisdom tooth becomes infected causes other dental problems, you may experience some of these symptoms:</p>\r\n								<ul>\r\n								<li>Red or swollen gums</li><br>\r\n								<li>Tender or bleeding gums</li><br>\r\n								<li>Jaw pain</li><br>\r\n								<li>Swelling around the jaw</li><br>\r\n								<li>Bad breath</li><br>\r\n								<li>An unpleasant taste in your mouth</li><br>\r\n								<li>Difficulty opening your mouth</li>\r\n								</ul>\r\n								<p>We have the expertise to conduct minor surgical procedure to take out the impacted wisdom tooth under anesthesia.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item emergency_dental_treatment">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Dental Avulsion</h3>\r\n								<p>It is the complete displacement of a tooth from its normal socket position in bone leading to intense pain. The treatment for teeth avulsion is re-plantation, as soon as possible. Re-plantation with composite help to re-establish the blood supply and to keep the tooth strong and stable.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Emergency Dental Treatment</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Clear Correct</h3>\r\n								<p>ClearCorrect is the clear and simple way to straighten your teeth without wearing braces so you can show off your smile! Looking for an alternative to braces? ClearCorrect is the clear and simple choice. No wires. No brackets. Just clear, convenient comfort—every reason to smile. With ClearCorrect, your dentist can straighten your teeth using a series of clear, custom, removable aligners. Each aligner moves your teeth just a little bit at a time until you eventually get straight teeth.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Invisalign</h3>\r\n								<p>Invisalign is at the forefront of cosmetic dentistry technology. Unlike the more traditional braces or retainers, Invisalign is a virtually invisible method of straightening your teeth. You will be fitted with removable, see-through aligners that have been specifically crafted to fit your teeth.</p>\r\n								<p>The aligners will gradually cause your teeth to shift their position slightly over a period of two -Four weeks. Every two - Four weeks, you will change the aligners for a new set that will cause your teeth to move a little more. As the treatment progresses over the following weeks and months, your teeth will straighten into their proper positions, as prescribed by your dental practitioner.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Fastbraces</h3>\r\n								<p>Dental Today is proud to be New Zealand’s premier dental office to offer the amazing Fastbraces Technology. Call or email us to discover how Dental Today and Fastbraces Technology can team up to give you a smile that you have always dreamed of.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Philip Zoom Whitening</h3>\r\n								<p>Philips Zoom professional whitening is a fast, effective and safe way to whiten your teeth. Results from professional treatments can be immediate (up to 8 shades whiter in 1 hour), and because a dental professional is involved, the process is safe, reliable and hassle free.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Replace discolored fillings</h3>\r\n								<p>At times white fillings collect staining or change color over time, especially at the edges. Therefore filling need to be replaced to match in with the teeth. We undertake replacement of discolored fillings job.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Cosmetic Re-Contouring</h3>\r\n								<p>Cosmetic re-contouring is the process of re-shaping chipped, crooked, cracked or not aligned teeth. This involves slight change, alters in shape or position of the teeth with an orthodontic treatment. All these options are cost effective and long lasting and give immediate results. Call us and book in for a free consultation to know more.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item affordable_cosmetic_services">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Crowns that look like teeth</h3>\r\n								<p>A crown or cap is a type of dental restoration procedure that fully or partly covers the portion of a tooth with a transparent material. Once implanted it acts as the outer covering of the teeth and look like a teeth. By doing a crown, you will be binding ot holding the whole teeth together thereby increasing its strength and life. The complete treatment is done in two steps with a time interval of two weeks. In the first step, the teeth to be caped or crowned are prepared for the crown, impressions are taken and a temporary crown is cemented. In the second step permanent crown is cemented.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag"> Affordable Cosmetic Services</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item smile_makeovers">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Tooth Jewellery</h3>\r\n								<p>We undertake all type of jobs related to tooth jewellery, right from diamond studs to well shaped gold teeth just to have that twinkle on your teeth when you smile.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Smile Makeovers</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item smile_makeovers">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Teeth Whitening</h3>\r\n								<p>Teeth whitening process lighten up color of your teeth and help to get rid of discoloration and stains. This need to be repeated at regular interval to maintain the brighter color of your teeth. We also offer take home kits which can help you whiten your teeth at your comfort station.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Smile Makeovers</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 serv-item isotope-item smile_makeovers">\r\n							<div class="serv-item-text">\r\n								<h3>Stain Removal</h3>\r\n								<p>Teeth looses it original color due to wear and tear with time, apart from that they turn pale yellow due to stains from coffee, tea, wine and smoking. These stains can be clean and restore the original sparkling smile on your face in just two sittings by deploying state of the art polishing dentistry at The Dental Hub.</p>\r\n								<div class="serv-item-tag">Smile Makeovers</div>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>'),
(4, 'staff.php', '<div class="page-title page-title-doctor bg-pattern" data-bgcolor="2BAAA1">\r\n        <div class="page-title-overlay">\r\n            <div class="container">\r\n            <div class="row">\r\n                <ol class="breadcrumb">\r\n                    <li class="breadcrumb-home"><a href="index.php"><i class="fa fa-home"></i></a></li>\r\n                    <li class="active">Our Staff</li>\r\n                </ol>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n	<!--\r\n        ====================\r\n        START: MOBILE DESIGN\r\n        ====================\r\n    -->\r\n	<a href="tel:09 218 7777" class="fancybox-2 btn btn-default hidden-sm hidden-md hidden-lg hidden-xlg" id="header-call-button-spacing">\r\n            CALL US\r\n        </a>\r\n    <!--\r\n        ==================\r\n        END: MOBILE DESIGN\r\n        ==================\r\n    -->\r\n\r\n    <div class="doctors-text">\r\n        <div class="container">\r\n            <div class="row">\r\n\r\n                <h2 class="section-title text-center">\r\n                    <span class="bold700">\r\n                    Friendly Staff\r\n                    </span>\r\n                </h2>\r\n                \r\n                <!-- Staff 01 -->\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 single-staff-panel">\r\n                    <div class="doctors-text-doctor">\r\n                        <img src="assets/images/staff/shivam.jpg" alt="" />\r\n                        <div class="doctors-text-doctor-name">Shivam Verma</div>\r\n                        <div class="doctors-text-doctor-position">Owner</div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="doctors-text-right">\r\n                    <p>Being the owner and business manager of The Dental Hub, Shivam works hard to ensure that the patients maximise their dental benefits and the claims are filed appropriately and in a timely manner. His warm, friendly and easily approachable attitude keeps his staff motivated to perform better.</p>\r\n                    <p>With more than 15 years of professional experience, he always strives to walk that extra mile to make each patient feel part of the family and ensures every patient derives complete satisfaction from the treatment.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <!-- Staff 02 -->\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 single-staff-panel">\r\n                    <div class="doctors-text-left">\r\n                    <p>Dr. Lowe has worked as a Dentist in the Hospital Services Dental Department at Wellington Hospital and rendered his services as Dental Surgeon in the Medical and Health, Dental Services Department, Hong Kong.</p>\r\n                    <p>He has served the Dental Profession as a Committee member and then as the President of the Auckland Branch of the New Zealand Association, and also acted as a full time self-employed Dentist in West Auckland.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="doctors-text-doctor">\r\n                        <img src="assets/images/staff/jeffery.jpg" alt="" />\r\n                        <div class="doctors-text-doctor-name">Dr. Jeffery Lowe</div>\r\n                        <div class="doctors-text-doctor-position">Dentist</div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n                <!-- Staff 03 -->\r\n                <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 single-staff-panel">\r\n                    <div class="doctors-text-doctor">\r\n                        <img src="assets/images/staff/nikita.jpg" alt="" />\r\n                        <div class="doctors-text-doctor-name">Dr. Nikita Verma</div>\r\n                        <div class="doctors-text-doctor-position">Owner</div>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="doctors-text-right">